Manchester United would sign Harry Maguire from Leicester City over the summer. Maguire is said to have cost United £80m, which is believed to be a world-record fee for a central defender. Maguire would then go on to start all five of Man United’s opening Premier League games of the 2019/20 campaign. United would keep two clean sheets in those games vs Chelsea and Leicester.   Good luck to @lcfc for the rest of the season… thanks for the reception 🤷🏻‍♂️😂 A post shared by  Harry Maguire (@harrymaguire93) on Sep 14, 2019 at 11:08am PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js The Red Devils would keep just seven clean sheets in the entire 2018/19 PL season so to have two in five this time around does look to have been an improvement. LIVERPOOL, ENGLAND – APRIL 21: Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, Manager of Manchester United looks on during the Premier League match between Everton FC and Manchester United at Goodison Park on April 21, 2019 in Liverpool, United Kingdom. (Photo by Jan Kruger/Getty Images) Manchester United’s latest game saw them take on West Ham United on Sunday, September 22nd. Ahead of the game with Wets Ham, Solskjaer had been speaking about Maguire. OGS stated that he has already started thinking about the England international as a future captain: “He is already been in my head thinking about him as a future captain. “He’s a leader on the pitch, he has a presence in both boxes. He is vocal, he’s a top, top professional. “I’m very pleased with the money we’ve spent on him.” As quoted by the Mirror. Maguire would start in Man United’s clash with West Ham. As of writing, United are currently 1-0 down to West Ham, meaning they will not be getting their 3rd PL clean sheet of the season. It would be Andriy Yarmolenko who put West Ham 1-0 up just before half-time. See also: Chelsea vs Liverpool betting tips: Premier League preview & predictions Arsenal vs Aston Villa betting tips: Premier League match preview and predictions Source: Great Goals